- By Geography: North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Middle East and Africa, South America

Virtual reality (VR) technology in the health market is expected to witness significant growth by 2029 due to the increasing adoption of advanced technologies in the healthcare sector. The hardware segment is projected to dominate the market as there is a growing demand for VR devices and accessories. On the other hand, the software segment is also anticipated to showcase substantial growth as healthcare facilities are investing in VR software for various applications such as surgery, education, rehabilitation, cognitive training, and more. Hospitals and surgical centers are the key end-users of VR technology in the health market, followed by research institutes, rehabilitation centers, and others. Geographically, North America is expected to lead the global VR health market, followed by Europe, Asia-Pacific, Middle East and Africa, and South America, owing to the increasing adoption of VR technology in the healthcare sector in these regions.

